FBIS3-30111 "dreas038_a_94017" FBIS-EAS-94-038 Document Type:Daily Report 25 February 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Ministry Lifts Evacuation Advisory on Serbia OW2502120994 Tokyo KYODO in English 1125 GMT 25 Feb 94 OW2502120994 Tokyo KYODO Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Tokyo, Feb. 25 KYODO -- The Foreign Ministry on Friday lifted an advisory that had recommended that Japanese nationals evacuate the former Yugoslav states of Serbia and Montenegro. The move followed a decision by the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (Nato) to forego air strikes against Bosnian Serb positions on the hills surrounding Sarajevo. An advisory cautioning against travel to Serbia and Montenegro remains in force, the ministry said.
